description: A U.S. Air Force leader in Niger made a whistleblower complaint to Congress raising alarm over the Biden administration’s reluctance to heed an eviction notice.
title: Defying Niger exit order leaves U.S. troops vulnerable, whistleblower says

description: A high-profile prison escape. A TV station takeover. An assault on police. Today on “Post Reports,” how powerful gangs in Ecuador pushed this historically peaceful nation to the brink and led its new president to declare war.
title: How a narco revolt pushed a peaceful nation to the brink

description: U.S. officials say that President Nicolás Maduro has not upheld his end of the bargain to allow free and fair elections.
title: Biden administration to reimpose oil and gas sanctions on Venezuela

description: Érika de Souza Vieira Nunes told investigators that Paulo Roberto Braga was alive when they entered the bank in Rio de Janeiro, police said. She’s been charged with theft by fraud and abusing a corpse.
title: Woman accused of wheeling dead ‘uncle’ into bank to sign loan

description: Iran’s first direct attack on Israel demonstrated the advances of its domestic weapons program, analysts said, while also exposing the limits of its arsenal.
title: What Iran’s attack on Israel revealed about its weapons arsenal

description: U.S.-funded groups in Italy have been pushing for greater restrictions on abortion in the country, and many doctors won’t perform the procedure.
title: Italy moves to pass law allowing antiabortion groups inside clinics

description: With a U.S. aid package stalled in Congress, Russia has exploited Ukraine’s ammunition and air defense shortages, destroying energy infrastructure across the country.
title: Russia hits Chernihiv, killing 17 as Ukraine pleads for air defense

description: The ruling party, Georgian Dream, has advanced a bill on “foreign agents” that critics say is itself a tool of Russian interference and that has sparked huge protests.
title: Georgia pushes Russian-style ‘foreign agent’ law, putting E.U. bid at risk

description: After Brittany Higgins accused her colleague Bruce Lehrmann of rape, he sued a TV network for airing her story. The case’s dismissal caps a years-long legal saga.
title: A rape took place in Parliament, judge rules in case that consumed Australia

description: In a single day, at least 120 people were killed in Ecuador’s deadliest prison battle. One inmate witnessed the gang fighting up close.
title: The prison battle that led to a gang war

description: Russia’s Foreign Ministry has been gathering data on the vulnerabilities of its Western adversaries, a classified Russian document shows.
title: Secret Russian foreign policy document urges action to weaken the U.S.

description: Washington plans to impose new sanctions to “degrade Iran’s military capacity” after Iran fired drones and missiles at Israel, the top U.S. security adviser said.
title: Middle East conflict live updates: U.S. and Europe weigh sanctions against Iran after its attack on Israel

description: In the military exercise, U.S. and Philippine troops will perform joint operations off the northern tip of the island of Luzon, facing Taiwan.
title: Philippines plans ambitious exercise with U.S. as concerns over China grow

description: These disparate countries have been driven together through a combination of factors, including U.S. sanctions. Ripping them apart will be far harder.
title: The desperate alignment of Russia, China, Iran and North Korea
